<taxonomicName authority="Bily." authorityName="Bily." box="[951,1136,1907,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ankareus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luciphilus">
<taxonomicName box="[951,1079,1907,1929]" genus="A." pageId="5" pageNumber="580" rank="species" species="luciphilus">
<emphasis box="[951,1079,1907,1929]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="580">
A. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bily" authorityName="Bily" box="[979,1079,1907,1929]" pageId="5" pageNumber="580" rank="species" species="luciphilus">luciphilus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bílý.
</taxonomicName>
(All figures at approximately same scale. Scale bar = 0.5 mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The aedeagus of this species is very different from that of the seven species from Arabia and Africa mentioned above and 
<taxonomicName box="[401,529,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ankareus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellamyi">
<emphasis box="[401,529,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">A. bellamyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (
<figureCitation box="[553,690,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[375,1208,597,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[370,1216,591,1823]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 19. Aedeagus (Figures 15 – 19 after the original species description publications). 11. A. natalensis Bellamy, Port St. John; 12. A. relictus (Bílý), Thanomah; 13. A. bellamyi, holotype; 14. A. bilyi, holotype; 15. A. transvaalensis Bellamy; 16. A. capensis Bellamy; 17. A. kenyensis Bellamy; 18. A. somalicus Bellamy; 19. A. luciphilus Bílý. (All figures at approximately same scale. Scale bar = 0.5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Figs. 11–19</figureCitation>
). From the original descriptions and specimens I have seen of the species described from Arabia and Africa, only 
<taxonomicName box="[731,884,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ankareus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis box="[731,884,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">A. tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has imbricate or round to polygonal pronotal sculpture similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[468,551,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ankareus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilyi">
<emphasis box="[468,485,260,283]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[501,551,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">bilyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Many species of Australian 
<taxonomicName authority="Cobos, 1957" authorityName="Cobos" authorityYear="1957" box="[893,1160,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Helferella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[893,1006,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Helferella</emphasis>
Cobos, 1957
</taxonomicName>
have a similar pronotal sculpture (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[319,587,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" refString="Williams, G. A. &amp; Weir, T. A. (1987) Four new species and new records of Australian Mastogeniinae (Coleoptera: Buprestidae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society, 26 (2), 153 - 159. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1440 - 6055.1987. tb 00277. x" type="journal article" year="1987">Williams &amp; Weir 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[601,661,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" refString="Williams, G. A. &amp; Weir, T. A. (1988) Further new species of Australian Mastogeniinae (Coleoptera: Buprestidae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society, 27, 179 - 181." type="journal article" year="1988">1988</bibRefCitation>
). I have examined the female 
<typeStatus box="[1018,1116,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1160,1309,296,319]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ankareus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis box="[1160,1309,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">A. tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has imbricate pronotal microsculpture at the centre with the sculpture laterally forming incipient polygonal cells (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10. 7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[451,1209,360,1317]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[370,1217,355,1329]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. 7. Dorsal habitus of A. bilyi, holotype; 8. Dorsal habitus of A. tsavoensis Bellamy, holotype; 9. Pronotum of A. bilyi, holotype; 10. Pronotum of A. tsavoensis Bellamy, holotype. (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256774/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[367,448,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ankareus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilyi">
<emphasis box="[367,384,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[398,448,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">bilyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as shown in Table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after my friend and colleague Svata Bílý for his help over the years in the loan of specimens and identifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,260,518,540]" box="[151,260,518,540]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,518,540]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">TABLE 1.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<table box="[159,1414,567,949]" gridcols="3" gridrows="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<tr box="[159,1414,567,590]" gridrow="0" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<th box="[159,362,567,590]" gridcol="0" gridrow="0" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Character</th>
<th box="[440,907,567,590]" gridcol="1" gridrow="0" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<taxonomicName box="[440,513,567,589]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ankareus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilyi">
<emphasis box="[440,513,567,589]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">A. bilyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</th>
<th box="[941,1414,567,590]" gridcol="2" gridrow="0" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<taxonomicName box="[941,1073,568,590]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ankareus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis box="[941,1073,568,590]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
A. 
<taxonomicName box="[969,1073,569,590]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">tsavoensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</th>
</tr>
<tr box="[159,1414,609,661]" gridrow="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<th box="[159,362,609,661]" gridcol="0" gridrow="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Elytral pubescence</th>
<td box="[440,907,609,661]" gridcol="1" gridrow="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Densely clothed with fairly long, pale, brown, curved, adpressed setae (Fig. 7)</td>
<td box="[941,1414,609,661]" gridcol="2" gridrow="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Nearly glabrous with sparse, short, dark, erect, inconspicuous bristle-like setae (Fig. 8)</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[159,1414,681,733]" gridrow="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<th box="[159,362,681,733]" gridcol="0" gridrow="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Elytral punctation</th>
<td box="[440,907,681,733]" gridcol="1" gridrow="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Moderately dense, with transverse rugose sculpture (Fig. 7)</td>
<td box="[941,1414,681,733]" gridcol="2" gridrow="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Not very dense, without transverse rugose sculpture (Fig. 8)</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[159,1414,753,836]" gridrow="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<th box="[159,362,753,836]" gridcol="0" gridrow="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Pronotal sculpture</th>
<td box="[440,907,753,836]" gridcol="1" gridrow="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Almost entirely composed of round to polygonal cells (Fig. 9)</td>
<td box="[941,1414,753,836]" gridcol="2" gridrow="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Mostly composed of transverse ridges, except laterally where it forms incipient polygonal cells (Fig. 10)</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[159,1414,855,908]" gridrow="4" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<th box="[159,362,855,908]" gridcol="0" gridrow="4" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Colour of upperside</th>
<td box="[440,907,855,908]" gridcol="1" gridrow="4" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Black with a slight greenish bronze reflection (Fig. 7)</td>
<td box="[941,1414,855,908]" gridcol="2" gridrow="4" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Shiny black with a distinct blue to green reflection (Fig. 8)</td>
</tr>
<tr box="[159,1414,927,949]" gridrow="5" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<th box="[159,362,927,949]" gridcol="0" gridrow="5" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Length</th>
<td box="[440,907,927,949]" gridcol="1" gridrow="5" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">3.51 mm</td>
<td box="[941,1414,927,949]" gridcol="2" gridrow="5" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">2.66 mm</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
